The paper focuses on the Union-Find problem, which is a fundamental data structure problem in computer science. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also evaluates the performance of several algorithms across different platforms and workloads, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces new techniques to reduce computational cost and uses Transactional Memory (TM) to optimize the algorithm, which could place it in the cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.AR (Architecture) sub-categories, respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the practical performance of the algorithms, which could also make it relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
